      • valid

        public static boolean valid(IdNumber idNumber)
        Standard validity check for Danish idNumbers. This method does not perform modulus validation as Danish CPR numbers issued after year 2007 do not necessarily pass the modulus test. Valid id number is expected in the following format: ddMMyyCxxG where:
        • ddMMyy: day of birth
        • C: century part. The combination of yy and C decide the exact year
        • xx: a serial number
        • G: gender part. Odd numbers represent males, while even numbers represent female.
        See official documentation or Wikipedia for more information.
        Parameters:
        idNumber - The idNumber to validate.
        Returns:
        true when valid id number, based on a given specification for Denmark.

      • validateModulus11

        public static boolean validateModulus11(IdNumber idNumber)
        Validity check for Danish idNumbers that performs modulus 11 test. Note that Danish CPR numbers issued after year 2007 do not necessarily pass the modulus test, but can still be valid. Valid id number is expected in the following format: ddMMyyCxxG where:
        • ddMMyy: day of birth
        • C: century part. The combination of yy and C decide the exact year
        • xx: a serial number
        • G: gender part and modulus 11 check number. Odd numbers represent males, while even numbers represent female.
        See official documentation or Wikipedia for more information.
        Parameters:
        idNumber - The idNumber to validate.
        Returns:
        true when valid id number, based on a given specification for Denmark.

      • gender

        public static Optional<Gender> gender(IdNumber idNumber)
        Extracts the optional gender from the given person number following the specification for the Danish CPR number. Note that this method doesn't check the validity of the idNumber, it merely extracts gender bit of idNumber and interprets it.
        Parameters:
        idNumber - where gender is taken from.
        Returns:
        Optional gender (male or female), or empty in case of non-digit gender bit.

      • birthday

        public static Optional<LocalDate> birthday(IdNumber idNumber)
        Calculates optional birthday for the given id number. Calculation is based on 7 first characters of the idNumber where the 7th character represents century.
        Parameters:
        idNumber - where birthday is calculated from.
        Returns:
        optional birthday, or empty in case of invalid date or invalid idNumber format.
